{"title_page": "The Flash (season 2)", "text_new": "{{short description|Season of television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox television season\n | bgcolour      = #1D2229\n | season_number = 2\n | image         = The Flash season 2.jpg\n | caption       = Home media cover\n | starring      = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Grant Gustin]]\n* [[Candice Patton]]\n* [[Danielle Panabaker]]\n* [[Carlos Valdes (actor)|Carlos Valdes]]\n* [[Keiynan Lonsdale]]\n* [[Tom Cavanagh]]\n* [[Jesse L. Martin]]\n}}\n | country       = United States\n | num_episodes  = 23\n | network       = [[The CW]]\n | first_aired   = {{Start date|2015|10|6}}\n | last_aired    = {{End date|2016|5|24}}\n | episode_list  = List of The Flash episodes\n}}\nThe second season of the American television series ''[[The Flash (2014 TV series)|The Flash]]'', which is based on the [[DC Comics]] character [[Flash (Barry Allen)|Barry Allen / Flash]], sees [[Barry Allen (Arrowverse)|Barry]] recognized as a hero in [[Central City (Arrowverse)|Central City]] after saving the city, only to face a new threat from a [[Parallel universe (fiction)|parallel universe]] in the form of the speedster [[Hunter Zolomon (Arrowverse)|Zoom]], who seeks to eliminate everyone connected to the [[Speed Force]] throughout the [[Multiverse (DC Comics)|multiverse]]. It is set in the [[Arrowverse]], sharing continuity with the other television series of the universe, and is a spin-off of ''[[Arrow (TV series)|Arrow]]''. The season was produced by [[Greg Berlanti|Berlanti Productions]], [[Warner Bros. Television]], and [[DC Comics|DC Entertainment]], with [[Andrew Kreisberg]], [[Gabrielle Stanton]], [[Aaron and Todd Helbing|Aaron Helbing]], and [[Aaron and Todd Helbing|Todd Helbing]] serving as [[showrunners]].\n\nThe season was ordered in January 2015, and filmed from that July to the following April in Vancouver. [[Grant Gustin]] stars as Barry, alongside principal cast members [[Candice Patton]], [[Danielle Panabaker]], [[Carlos Valdes (actor)|Carlos Valdes]], [[Tom Cavanagh]], and [[Jesse L. Martin]] also returning from the [[The Flash (season 1)|first season]], and are joined by [[Keiynan Lonsdale]]. This season also introduces characters from ''[[Legends of Tomorrow]]'', which was being developed as a spin-off.\n\nThe first episode of the season premiered on October 6, 2015, with the season, consisting of 23 episodes, airing on [[The CW]] until May 24, 2016. The premiere was watched by 3.58&nbsp;million viewers, down from the first-season premiere but average for the series. The second season of ''The Flash'' received universal acclaim from critics, and finished as the 112th ranked show, slightly up from season one, with an average viewership of 4.25&nbsp;million. The series was renewed for a [[The Flash (season 3)|third season]] on March 11, 2016.<ref name=\"S3Renew\" />\n\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{See also|List of The Flash episodes}}\n<onlyinclude>{{Episode table |background=#1D2229 |overall=5 |season=5 |title=19 |director=13 |writer=32 |airdate=10 |prodcode=7 |viewers=9 |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Flash (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 24\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = The Man Who Saved Central City\n |DirectedBy      = [[Ralph Hemecker]]\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=[[Greg Berlanti]] & [[Andrew Kreisberg]]|t=Andrew Kreisberg & [[Gabrielle Stanton]]}}\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|10|6}}\n |ProdCode        = 3J5651\n |Viewers         = 3.58<ref name=\"2.01\">{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/07/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-6-2015/477169/ |title=Tuesday Final Ratings: 'The Muppets', 'NCIS' and 'Scream Queens' Adjusted Up; 'Flash' and 'iZombie' Hold |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=October 7, 2015 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6c6vRBlan?url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/07/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-6-2015/477169/ |archive-date=October 7, 2015 |access-date=October 7, 2015}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = [[Ronnie Raymond (Arrowverse)|Ronnie]] and [[Martin Stein (Arrowverse)|Stein]] turn into Firestorm and help [[Barry Allen (Arrowverse)|Barry]] destroy the singularity, but at the cost of Ronnie's life. Six months later, Barry operates alone, using his speed to repair [[Central City (Arrowverse)|Central City]] while being embraced by the public as a hero; [[Cisco Ramon (Arrowverse)|Cisco]] works in the police department alongside [[Joe West (Arrowverse)|Joe]], and [[Caitlin Snow (Arrowverse)|Caitlin]] works at Mercury Labs. Barry evaluates a crime scene with a victim named [[Albert Rothstein (Arrowverse)|Al Rothstein]]. At a ceremony, the Flash is attacked by Atom-Smasher, whose strength and size manipulation prove too much for Barry, but manages to force his mask off. Underneath the mask Atom-Smasher is revealed to look exactly like Rothstein. Barry is convinced by Joe and the others that he needs help in taking down certain metahumans and Rothstein is defeated by over absorbing [[radiation]]. As he dies, Rothstein tells Barry that he was sent to kill him by someone called \"[[Hunter Zolomon (Arrowverse)|Zoom]]\". Barry receives a flash memory from [[Harrison Wells]]' ([[Eobard Thawne (Arrowverse)|Eobard Thawne]]) lawyer containing his confession to killing [[Nora Allen (Arrowverse)|Nora]]. [[Henry Allen (The Flash)|Henry]] is exonerated and released from prison, and leaves Central City so that Barry can focus on being the Flash. A man arrives at [[S.T.A.R. Labs (Arrowverse)|S.T.A.R. Labs]] and, introducing himself as [[Jay Garrick (Arrowverse)|Jay Garrick]], tells the team their world is in danger.\n |LineColor       = 1D2229\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Flash (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 25\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Flash of Two Worlds\n |DirectedBy      = [[Jesse Warn]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Aaron and Todd Helbing|Aaron Helbing & Todd Helbing]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|10|13}}\n |ProdCode        = 3J5652\n |Viewers         = 3.49<ref name=\"2.02\">{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/14/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-13-2015/478601/ |title=Tuesday final ratings: 'The Flash' and 'NCIS' adjusted up, 'Chicago Fire' holds |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=October 14, 2015 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6cHYvbN9k?url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/14/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-13-2015/478601/ |archive-date=October 14, 2015 |access-date=October 14, 2015}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Jay explains to everyone that he is the Flash on a parallel Earth and that he was in a battle with a demonic speedster named Zoom when the singularity brought him to this Earth without his powers. Stein confirms the claim, describing their world as \"Earth-1\" and Jay's as \"Earth-2\". Zoom brings another metahuman from Earth-2 called Sand Demon, later identified as Eddie Slick, to kill the Flash. Cisco analyzes the \"sand\" left behind and has a vision of the previous fight, frightening him. After Slick kidnaps Officer [[Patty Spivot (Arrowverse)|Patty Spivot]], Jay teaches Barry how to hurl lightning. Cisco uses his power to find Patty's location. Barry uses the lightning blast to turn Sand Demon's particles to glass, killing him. Patty reveals to Joe that [[Mark Mardon (Arrowverse)|Mark Mardon]] killed her father. She joins Joe's metahuman task force. Cisco divulges his ability to Stein, and convinces him not to tell anyone. Stein and Cisco are able to locate 52 breaches with the Earth-2, with the largest one being within S.T.A.R. Labs itself. Joe's estranged wife, Francine, pays him a visit. Stein collapses while talking. On Earth-2 it is revealed that the Harrison Wells of that world is alive and in charge of S.T.A.R. Labs.\n |LineColor       = 1D2229\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Flash (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 26\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Family of Rogues\n |DirectedBy      = [[John F. Showalter]]\n |WrittenBy       = Julian Meiojas & Katherine Walczak\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|10|20}}\n |ProdCode        = 3J5653\n |Viewers         = 3.47<ref name=\"2.03\">{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/21/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-20-2015/479719/ |title=Tuesday final ratings: 'NCIS' and 'Limitless' adjusted up, 'Chicago Fire' adjusted down |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=October 21, 2015 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6cSQAQW37?url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/21/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-20-2015/479719/ |archive-date=October 22, 2015 |access-date=October 21, 2015}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Jay creates a device that stabilizes the singularity and will allow him to return home, but he opts to stay to help Barry stop Zoom. Meanwhile, [[Lisa Snart (Arrowverse)|Lisa Snart]] shows up asking for Flash's help in rescuing [[Leonard Snart (Arrowverse)|Snart]], whom she believes was kidnapped. Barry tracks down Snart, who is revealed not to be kidnapped but is working with his father, [[Lewis Snart|Lewis]]. Lisa states that Snart would never work with Lewis willingly, because the latter was abusive toward her when she was a child. Eventually, the team determines that Lewis placed a bomb inside of Lisa and threatened to kill her if Snart did not help him with his theft. Barry infiltrates Lewis' crew with assistance from Snart. Cisco successfully removes the bomb from Lisa, so Snart uses his cold gun to [[Parricide|kill his father]] in retaliation. Snart is incarcerated in Iron Heights and Lisa leaves. Joe reveals to Iris that Francine is alive and a former addict. Stein turns into Firestorm, but with blue flames. Earth-2's Wells arrives at the lab through the breach.\n |LineColor       = 1D2229\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Flash (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 27\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = The Fury of Firestorm\n |DirectedBy      = [[Stefan Pleszczynski]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Kai Wu|Kai Yu Wu]] & Joe Peracchio\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|10|27}}\n |ProdCode        = 3J5654\n |Viewers         = 3.43<ref name=\"2.04\">{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/28/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-27-2015/480890/ |title=Tuesday final ratings: 'Fresh Off the Boat', 'The Flash' and 'NCIS' adjust up, 'Wicked City' stays under 1.0 |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=October 28, 2015 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151030134708/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/28/tuesday-final-ratings-oct-27-2015/480890/ |archive-date=October 30, 2015 |access-date=October 28, 2015}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = The team is able to temporarily stabilize Stein. Caitlin states that he needs to merge with a new person in order to survive. She identifies two potential candidates: a scientist named [[Henry Hewitt (Arrowverse)|Henry Hewitt]] and a former high school [[American football|football]] star named [[Jefferson Jackson (Arrowverse)|Jefferson Jackson]]. Hewitt is excited to merge with Stein, but the attempt fails and Hewitt leaves angrily, not knowing that his own metahuman powers have been activated. Jefferson initially refuses, but agrees when Hewitt goes on rampage. After the successful merger, the new Firestorm joins Barry in helping to take down Hewitt, who is incarcerated. Before departing with Jefferson, Stein encourages Cisco to tell the others about his powers. Meanwhile, Francine reveals that she is suffering from a [[terminal illness]] and only has months to live. Iris later confronts her for hiding the existence of the former's brother. In the meantime, Wells breaks into Mercury Labs and steals an unknown device. Later, Barry is attacked by a [[King Shark (Arrowverse)|humanoid shark monster]] sent by Zoom, but is saved by Wells.\n |LineColor       = 1D2229\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Flash (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 28\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = The Darkness and the Light\n |DirectedBy      = [[Steve Shill]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Ben Sokolowski]] & [[Grainne Godfree]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2015|11|3}}\n |ProdCode        = 3J5655\n |Viewers         = 3.87<ref name=\"2.05\">{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/11/04/tuesday-final-ratings-fresh-off-the-boat-and-best-time-ever-adjust-up/ |title=Tuesday final ratings: 'Fresh Off the Boat' and 'Best Time Ever' adjust up |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=November 4, 2015 |website=[[TV by the Numbers]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6cndGsVPC?url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/11/04/tuesday-final-ratings-fresh-off-the-boat-and-best-time-ever-adjust-up/ |archive-date=November 4, 2015 |access-date=November 4, 2015}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Wells, who Cisco nicknames \"Harry\" to distinguish him from Thawne, reveals that he is responsible for the creation of the metahumans and Zoom on Earth-2. He states that he plans to help Barry's team stop Zoom and other metahumans. At the same time, a metahuman from Earth-2 called Doctor Light arrives and starts robbing banks. Barry recognizes her as the Earth-2 version of [[Linda Park (Arrowverse)|Linda]]. Later, Light attempts to kill Linda and take over her identity, but accidentally kills Linda's boss and is stopped by Barry's team in the process. Harry reveals Cisco's powers to the team, which Cisco uses to locate Light. Barry defeats her with the help of Harry. After locking Light up, they plan to use her to lure Zoom out and defeat him for good. Jay, who dislikes Harry and vice versa, thinks it is too dangerous and leaves the team. Meanwhile, Barry starts dating Patty while Cisco starts a date with a barista named [[Kendra Saunders (Arrowverse)|Kendra Saunders]]. Cisco picks the nickname \"Vibe\" for himself. Back on Earth-2, it is revealed that Zoom has [[Jesse Wells|Harry's daughter]] cap