nough]] as [[Damien Darhk (Arrowverse)|Damien Darhk]]<ref name=\"McDonough\" />\n*<!-- 208 -->[[Stephen Amell]] as [[Oliver Queen (Arrowverse)|Oliver Queen / Green Arrow]]<ref name=\"S2ArrowCrossover\" />\n*<!-- 208 -->[[Willa Holland]] as [[Thea Queen]] / [[Speedy (comics)|Speedy]]<ref name=\"S2ArrowCrossover\" />\n*<!-- 209 -->[[Liam McIntyre]] as [[Mark Mardon (Arrowverse)|Mark Mardon / Weather Wizard]]<ref name=\"McIntyre\" />\n*<!-- 209 -->[[Mark Hamill]] as [[James Jesse (Arrowverse)|James Jesse / Trickster]]<ref name=\"Hamill\" />\n*<!-- 210 -->[[Aaron Douglas (actor)|Aaron Douglas]] as [[Russell Glosson|Russel Glosson / Turtle]]<ref name=\"Douglas\" />\n*<!-- 210 -->[[Matt Letscher]] as [[Eobard Thawne (Arrowverse)|Eobard Thawne / Reverse-Flash]]<ref name=\"Letscher\" />\n*<!-- 212 -->[[Marco Grazzini]] as [[Joey Monteleone (Arrowverse)|Joey Monteleone / Tar Pit]]<ref name=\"Grazzini\" />\n*<!-- 213 -->[[Adam Stafford]] as [[Adam Fells (Arrowverse)|Adam Fells / Geomancer]]<ref name=\"Stafford\" />\n*<!-- 213 -->[[Haig Sutherland]] as [[Griffin Grey (Arrowverse)|Griffin Grey]]<ref name=\"Sutherland\" />\n*<!-- 213 -->[[Michael Rowe (actor)|Michael Rowe]] as [[Floyd Lawton (Arrowverse)|Floyd Lawton]]<ref name=\"Earth-2 doppelgangers\" />\n*<!-- 214 -->[[Tone Bell]] as [[Scott Evans (Arrowverse)|Scott Evans]]<ref name=\"Bell\" />\n*<!-- 215 -->[[Audrey Marie Anderson]] as [[Lyla Michaels (Arrowverse)|Lyla Michaels]]<ref name=\"Anderson\" />\n*<!-- 216 -->Allison Paige as [[Eliza Harmon (Arrowverse)|Eliza Harmon / Trajectory]]<ref name=\"Paige\" />\n*<!-- 217 -->[[Andy Mientus]] as [[Hartley Rathaway (Arrowverse)|Hartley Rathaway / Pied Piper]]<ref name=\"Mientus\" />\n*<!-- 221 -->Michelle Harrison as [[Nora Allen (Arrowverse)|Nora Allen]]<ref name=\"Harrison\" />\n**<!-- 213 -->Harrison also voices Nora Allen's Earth-2 doppelg\u00e4nger<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.inverse.com/article/11274-the-flash-goes-to-earth-2-for-opposite-day-and-it-s-more-than-a-novelty |title='The Flash' in Earth-2 Is More Than Just Opposite Day |last=Francisco |first=Eric |date=February 10, 2016 |website=[[Inverse (website)|Inverse]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20181220065244/https://www.inverse.com/article/11274-the-flash-goes-to-earth-2-for-opposite-day-and-it-s-more-than-a-novelty |archive-date=December 20, 2018 |access-date=December 17, 2018}}</ref>\n*<!-- 222 -->[[Katie Cassidy]] as [[Laurel Lance (Arrowverse Earth-2)|Laurel Lance / Black Siren]]<ref name=\"BlackSiren\" />\n}}\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Development ===\nOn January 11, 2015, ''The Flash'' was renewed for a second season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/01/11/arrow-jane-the-virgin-reign-the-100-the-flash-the-originals-the-vampire-diaries-renewed-by-the-cw/349027/ |title='Arrow', 'Jane The Virgin', 'Reign', 'The 100', 'The Flash', 'Supernatural, 'The Originals' & 'The Vampire Diaries' Renewed by the CW |last=Bibel |first=Sara |date=January 11, 2015 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150111232833/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/01/11/arrow-jane-the-virgin-reign-the-100-the-flash-the-originals-the-vampire-diaries-renewed-by-the-cw/349027/ |archive-date=January 11, 2015 |access-date=January 11, 2015}}</ref> With the commencement of production on the season, former ''[[Arrow (TV series)|Arrow]]'' and ''[[Ugly Betty]]'' writer [[Gabrielle Stanton]] was promoted to executive producer and showrunner; after having served as consulting producer and writer on the [[The Flash (season 1)|first season]]'s finale \"Fast Enough\".<ref name=\"Stanton1\">{{Cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2015/08/17/once-upon-a-time-season-5-belle-merida-spoilers/ |title=Matt's Inside Line: Scoop on Once, Arrow, Castle, The Flash, Scandal, Gotham, Reign, Haven and More |last=Webb Mitovich |first=Matt |date=August 17, 2015 |website=[[TVLine]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150818064756/http://tvline.com/2015/08/17/once-upon-a-time-season-5-belle-merida-spoilers/ |archive-date=August 18, 2015 |access-date=August 18, 2015}}</ref> However, it was later reported that series co-creator [[Andrew Kreisberg]] would be returning to sole showrunner duties at an unspecified time.<ref name=\"THRdeal\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/andrew-kreisberg-deal-warner-bros-831387 |title='The Flash' Boss Andrew Kreisberg Inks Overall Deal With Warner Bros. TV (Exclusive) |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |date=November 3, 2013 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151106004350/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/andrew-kreisberg-deal-warner-bros-831387 |archive-date=November 6, 2015 |access-date=November 3, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ew.com/article/2015/09/10/flash-season-2-jay-zoom-wally-spoilers/ |title=The Flash season 2: New characters revealed by showrunner Andrew Kreisberg: Spoilers |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=September 10, 2015 |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170204221213/http://ew.com/article/2015/09/10/flash-season-2-jay-zoom-wally-spoilers/ |archive-date=February 4, 2017 |access-date=January 20, 2017}}</ref> That time was later proved to be at the start of 2016, \"Potential Energy\", when Stanton was no longer credited as being involved with the show.<ref name=\"Potential Energy\">{{Cite episode |title=Potential Energy |series=The Flash |series-link=The Flash (2014 TV series) |network=The CW |date=January 19, 2016 |season=2 |number=10}}</ref><ref name=\"Stanton quit\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbr.com/dark-confessions-arrowverse/ |title=15 BTS Stories About The Arrowverse (That Threatened To End It For Good) |last=Czap |first=Travis |date=March 6, 2018 |website=[[Comic Book Resources]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181217054003/https://www.cbr.com/dark-confessions-arrowverse/ |archive-date=December 17, 2018 |access-date=December 14, 2018}}</ref> [[Aaron and Todd Helbing]] also served as the season's showrunners.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.melty.com/the-flash-showrunner-promises-that-season-2-s-finale-will-be-packed-full-of-emotion-and-epicness-a4892.html |title=The Flash showrunner promises that Season 2's finale will be packed full of emotion and epicness |last=H. |first=Callum |date=April 29, 2016 |website=Melty |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202000935/http://www.melty.com/the-flash-showrunner-promises-that-season-2-s-finale-will-be-packed-full-of-emotion-and-epicness-a4892.html |archive-date=February 2, 2017 |access-date=January 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2017/05/22/aaron-helbing-off-the-flash-in-season-4/ |title=Aaron Helbing Off the Flash in Season 4 |last=Burlingame |first=Russ |date=May 22, 2017 |website=Comicbook.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181004131615/https://comicbook.com/dc/2017/05/22/aaron-helbing-off-the-flash-in-season-4/ |archive-date=October 4, 2018 |access-date=December 14, 2018}}</ref>\n<!--\n=== Writing ===\n* https://www.tvinsider.com/26163/grant-gustin-speeds-into-season-2-of-the-flash/\n* http://www.spoilertv.com/2015/05/the-flash-season-finale-post-mortem.html\n** http://ew.com/article/2015/05/19/flash-season-1-finale-eddie-death-rick-cosnett-spoilers/\n** http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/flash-finale-spoilers-eddie-thawne-796679\n* https://io9.gizmodo.com/the-major-theme-of-the-flash-season-2-how-a-superhero-1717341040\n* https://www.tvguide.com/news/the-flash-producers-reveal-plans-for-earth-two-killer-frost-and-more/\n**  https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/flash-producers-season-2-well-definitely-explore-earth-two\n* http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/legends-tomorrow-star-shares-spinoff-800147\n* https://movieweb.com/flash-season-2-legends-tomorrow-firestorm-robbi