st-season-2-crossover-grant-gustin/\n* http://comicbook.com/2015/10/21/the-flash-details-on-the-midseason-finale/\n* http://www.etonline.com/news/174383_the_flash_harrison_wells_earth_2_hes_a_dick_grant_gustin_tom_cavanagh\n* http://tvline.com/2015/10/26/the-flash-season-2-spoilers-new-firestorm/\n* http://www.cbr.com/the-flashs-kreisberg-panabaker-tease-caitlins-killer-frost-future-earth-2-more/\n* http://collider.com/the-flash-season-2-danielle-panabaker-andrew-kreisberg-interview/\n* http://collider.com/the-flash-season-2-interview-andrew-kreisberg-danielle-panabaker/\n* http://ew.com/article/2015/10/27/flash-wally-west-harrison-wells-spoilers/\n* http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/flash-west-family-shocker-834899\n* http://ca.ign.com/articles/2015/10/28/the-flash-producer-talks-wally-west-king-shark-and-the-next-arrow-crossover\n* http://tvline.com/gallery/tv-spoilers-2016-season-premieres-photos/#!8/winter-preview-flash-2/\n* https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/the-flash-reverse-flash-returns-eobard-thawne-alive-1201689164/\n* https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/the-flash-patty-barry-secret-identity-reverse-flash-1201689455/\n* http://ew.com/article/2016/02/05/spoiler-room-agents-shield-hawaii-five-0-once-upon-time-spoilers/\n* http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/flash-eps-earth-2-shockers-863428\n** http://collider.com/the-flash-season-2-escape-from-earth-2-preview/\n* http://ew.com/article/2016/02/23/flash-zoom-identity-jay-garrick-hunter-zolomon/\n* http://ew.com/article/2016/04/12/flash-zoom-hunter-zolomon-teddy-sears-spoilers/\n* http://ew.com/article/2016/04/15/spoiler-room-flash-greys-anatomy-blacklist-spoilers/\n* http://ew.com/article/2016/04/26/flash-barry-speed-powers-spoilers/\n* http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/flash-producers-tease-zooms-reign-887596\n* https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/the-flash-recap-season-2-episode-19-back-to-normal-1201760487/\n* http://collider.com/the-flash-season-2-andrew-kreisberg-tom-cavanagh-interview/\n* http://collider.com/the-flash-season-2-tom-cavanagh-andrew-kreisberg-interview/\n* http://www.eonline.com/photos/18668/2016-tv-finale-spoiler-rama/693616\n* https://web.archive.org/web/20160621034054/http://www.tvguide.com/special/finale-preview/spoilers/\n* http://tvline.com/gallery/may-sweeps-spoilers-2016-finale-episodes-photos/#!12/flash-may-sweeps/ -->\n\n=== Casting ===\nMain cast members [[Grant Gustin]], [[Candice Patton]], [[Danielle Panabaker]], [[Carlos Valdes (actor)|Carlos Valdes]] and [[Jesse L. Martin]] return from the first season as [[Barry Allen (Arrowverse)|Barry Allen / The Flash]], [[Iris West (Arrowverse)|Iris West]], [[Caitlin Snow (Arrowverse)|Caitlin Snow]], [[Cisco Ramon (Arrowverse)|Cisco Ramon / Vibe]] and [[Joe West (Arrowverse)|Joe West]], respectively.<ref name=\"TeamFlashS2\" /> [[Tom Cavanagh]], who portrayed [[Eobard Thawne (Arrowverse)|Eobard Thawne]] impersonating [[Harrison Wells]] in season one, also returned as a regular, playing Wells' Earth-2 doppelg\u00e4nger.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.etonline.com/news/174383_the_flash_harrison_wells_earth_2_hes_a_dick_grant_gustin_tom_cavanagh |title='The Flash' Cast Dishes on Harrison Wells' Return: 'He's a Dick' (and No One's Thrilled!) |last=Aguilera |first=Leanne |date=October 20, 2015 |website=[[Entertainment Tonight]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180608073732/https://www.etonline.com/news/174383_the_flash_harrison_wells_earth_2_hes_a_dick_grant_gustin_tom_cavanagh |archive-date=June 8, 2018 |access-date=December 2, 2018}}</ref> [[Rick Cosnett]], a main cast member from season one, did not return as a regular because his character, [[Eddie Thawne]], died in the season one finale.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/05/19/flash-season-1-finale-eddie-death-rick-cosnett-spoilers |title=The Flash boss on finale's shocking departure |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=May 19, 2015 |website=Entertainment Weekly |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818062820/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/05/19/flash-season-1-finale-eddie-death-rick-cosnett-spoilers |archive-date=August 18, 2016 |access-date=November 6, 2016}}</ref> He instead returned as a guest star in the season premiere \"The Man Who Saved Central City\" in a dream sequence,<ref name=\"collider S02E1 review\">{{Cite web |url=http://collider.com/the-flash-season-2-premiere-recap-the-man-who-saved-central-city/ |title='The Flash' Season 2 Premiere Recap: \"The Man Who Saved Central City\" |last=Trumbore |first=Dave |date=October 6, 2015 |website=Collider |language=en-US |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160514122552/http://collider.com/the-flash-season-2-premiere-recap-the-man-who-saved-central-city/ |archive-date=May 14, 2016 |access-date=December 2, 2018}}</ref> and later in the episode \"Flash Back\", where Barry travels back to a time when Eddie was still alive.<ref name=\"Cosnett\" /> In August 2015, [[Keiynan Lonsdale]] was cast as [[Wally West (Arrowverse)|Wally West]],<ref name=\"WallyFlashS2\" /> the unknown son of Joe, and Iris' brother.<ref name=\"KreisbergOct2015\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/kreisberg-panabaker-on-latest-flash-developments-and-west-family-revelations |title=Kreisberg & Panabaker on latest \"Flash\" Developments and West family revelations |last=Mahadeo |first=Kevin |date=October 27, 2015 |website=Comic Book Resources |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151029104448/http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/kreisberg-panabaker-on-latest-flash-developments-and-west-family-revelations |archive-date=October 29, 2015 |access-date=October 28, 2015}}</ref> Gustin, Patton, Panabaker, Valdes and Martin also portray the Earth-2 versions of their characters in the episode \"[[Welcome to Earth-2]]\",<ref name=\"Earth-2 doppelgangers\" /> while Cavanagh portrays Thawne impersonating the Earth-1 Wells in \"The Man Who Saved Central City\" and \"Flash Back\".<ref name=\"collider S02E1 review\" /><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/comic-riffs/wp/2016/03/30/flash-tv-recap-no-matter-his-earth-this-show-revolves-best-around-tom-cavanagh/ |title='Flash' TV recap: No matter his Earth, this show revolves best around Tom Cavanagh |last=Betancourt |first=David |date=March 30, 2016 |work=[[The Washington Post]] |access-date=December 17, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331150513/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/comic-riffs/wp/2016/03/30/flash-tv-recap-no-matter-his-earth-this-show-revolves-best-around-tom-cavanagh/ |archive-date=March 31, 2016}}</ref>\n\nDiscussing the casting of Lonsdale, Kreisberg stated, \"Just like when we met Grant [Gustin] for the first time, we instantly knew Keiynan embodied all the heart and courage of a hero. We are so excited to be bringing this much-beloved character onto the show.\"<ref name=\"WallyFlashS2\" /> It was always intended for Wally to be the son of Joe and brother of Iris, which differs from the character's comic history, as the producers disliked second seasons of television series that would introduce cousins of characters that were never previously mentioned, feeling it was \"weird\".<ref name=\"KreisbergOct2015\" /> Lonsdale originally auditioned for ''[[Legends of Tomorrow]]'' to portray Jefferson \"Jax\" Jackson.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/12/07/flash-wally-west-lonsdale-martin |title=The Flash stars talk Wally West introduction |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=December 7, 2015 |website=Entertainment Weekly |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151209082111/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/12/07/flash-wally-west-lonsdale-martin |archive-date=December 9, 2015 |access-date=December 8, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2015, it was announced that [[Teddy Sears]] would recur in the role of [[Jay Garrick (Arrowverse)|Jay Garrick]], the Flash of Earth-2.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/the-flash-jay-garrick-teddy-sears-season-2-1201538467/ |title='The Flash' Casts DC Comics' Jay Garrick, Patty Spivot for Season 2, Teases New Villain at Comic-Con |date=July 12, 2015 |work=Variety |access-date=December 2, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616103319/https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/the-flash-jay-garrick-teddy-sears-season-2-1201538467/ |archive-date=June 16, 2018}}</ref> However, later in the season it was revealed that his character was actually [[Hunter Zolomon (Arrowverse)|Hunter Zolomon / Zoom]] posing as Jay.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.avclub.com/tvclub/zoom-reveals-all-and-barry-powerless-stop-him-flas-235518 |title=Zoom reveals all and Barry is powerless to stop him on The Flash |date=April 19, 2016 |website=[[The A.V. Club]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170818065935/http://www.avclub.com/tvclub/zoom-reveals-all-and-barry-powerless-stop-him-flas-235518 |archive-date=August 18, 2017 |access-date=December 2, 2018}}</ref> Ryan Handley portrayed Zoom in costume prior to this revelation, while [[Tony Todd]] voiced Zoom.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2016/04/13/teddy-sears/ |title=Teddy Sears on What Makes The Flash Great, The Zoom Twist, and This Week's Big Episode |date=April 16, 2016 |website=Comicbook.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612135847/http://comicbook.com/dc/2016/04/13/teddy-sears/ |archive-date=June 12, 2018 |access-date=December 2, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"ZoomVoice\" />\n<!-- *http://tvline.com/2015/06/10/the-flash-season-2-barry-new-love-interest-felicity/\n*http://tvline.com/2015/06/11/the-flash-season-2-spoilers-cynical-new-hero/\n*http://tvline.com/2015/06/29/the-flash-season-2-spoilers-barry-iris-wendy/\n*http://comicbook.com/2015/07/11/jay-garrick-confirmed-for-the-flash-season-2/\n*https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/the-flash-zoom-tony-todd-season-2-villain-1201581891/\n*http://ew.com/article/2015/12/23/flash-matt-letscher-reverse-flash-return/\n**http://ew.com/article/2016/01/15/spoiler-room-mr-robot-greys-anatomy-flash-spoilers/\n*http://ew.com/article/2016/01/04/flash-robbie-amell-returning-deathstorm/\n*http://tvline.com/2016/03/10/walking-dead-season-6-daryl-carol-spoilers/\n*http://tvline.com/2016/04/04/the-flash-katie-cassidy-black-siren-earth-two/ -->\n\n=== Design ===\nMaya Mani replaced [[Colleen Atwood]] as the costume designer for the second season and made slight changes to the Flash costume, such as changing the color of his chest emblem from red to white, being faithful to the Flash costume from the comics.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://fashionista.com/2015/09/fall-tv-costume-design-october |title=Costume secrets from the upcoming seasons of 'Reign,' 'The Good Wife' and more |date=September 28, 2015 |website=Fashionista |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150929040254/http://fashionista.com/2015/09/fall-tv-costume-design-october |archive-date=September 29, 2015 |access-date=September 29, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/10/03/a-visual-history-of-the-flash |title=A Visual History of The Flash |last=Schedeen |first=Jesse |date=October 3, 2017 |website=IGN |at=slide 28 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181019205708/https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/10/03/a-visual-history-of-the-flash |archive-date=October 19, 2018 |access-date=December 2, 2018}}</ref> Gustin stated that, around the time of filming the season's ninth episode, \"we stopped gluing the mask to my face and switched to a mask that just slipped on and off with a zipper\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tvinsider.com/25346/outfitting-arrows-alter-egos-details-from-designer-maya-mani/ |title=Outfitting Arrow's Alter Egos: Details From Designer Maya Mani |last=Holbrook |first=Damian |date=August 18, 2015 |website=[[TV Insider]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708105448/https://www.tvinsider.com/25346/outfitting-arrows-alter-egos-details-from-designer-maya-mani/ |archive-date=July 8, 2017 |access-date=December 2, 2018}}</ref> While Zoom's costume in the comics is a verbatim replica of Eobard Thawne's yellow-and-red [[Reverse-Flash]] costume, the costume seen in the TV series is entirely in black.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://collider.com/the-flash-zoom-hunter-zolomon-comics/ |title='The Flash': Hunter Zolomon and Zoom's Comic Book Origins |last=Valentine |first=Evan |date=March 1, 2016 |website=Collider |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181217054003/http://collider.com/the-flash-zoom-hunter-zolomon-comics/ |archive-date=December 17, 2018 |access-date=December 2, 2018}}</ref> Kreisberg compared Zoom's appearance to that of the [[Marvel Comics]] character [[Venom (Marvel Comics character)|Venom]], saying, \"The Zoom outfit is much more organic than the Reverse-Flash suit. In a way, it's hard to tell if it is a suit or alive\u2026 There's no skin showing, for all you know there's a robot underneath, or dark energy.\"<ref name=\"ZoomVenom\">{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/the-flash-zoom-tony-todd-season-2-villain-1201581891/ |title='The Flash' Casts Tony Todd as Voice of DC Villain Zoom in Season 2 (EXCLUSIVE) |last=Prudom |first=Laura |date=August 31, 2015 |work=Variety |access-date=December 2, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150912040110/http://variety.com/2015/tv/news/the-flash-zoom-tony-todd-season-2-villain-1201581891/ |archive-date=September 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nProduction on the season began on July 7, 2015, in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]],<ref name=\"ProductionBegins\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/flash-season-2-filming-begins-july-firestorms-new-powers-barrys-new-love-will-make-iris-1505981 |title=The Flash season 2 filming begins in July: Firestorm's new powers and Barry's new love will make Iris jealous? |date=June 13, 2015 |website=IBTimes UK |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160105133537/http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/flash-season-2-filming-begins-july-firestorms-new-powers-barrys-new-love-will-make-iris-1505981 |archive-date=January 5, 2016 |access-date=October 26, 2016}}</ref> and concluded on April 18, 2016.<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=722103211767631872 |user=grantgust |title=Pretty sure Flash is back on tv tomorrow and today is my last day of filming for season 2. |author=Grant Gustin |author-link=Grant Gustin |date=April 18, 2016 |access-date=October 27, 2016}}</ref>\n<!-- * http://collider.com/the-flash-season-2-kevin-smith-gorilla-city-grodd/\n* http://ew.com/article/2016/05/10/flash-kevin-smith-director/ -->\n\n=== Music ===\nComposer [[Blake Neely]] returned as the primary composer for the second season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://comicbook.com/dc/2016/07/18/the-flash-season-2-soundtrack-details-announced/ |title=The Flash Season 2 Soundtrack Details Announced |last=Jayson |first=Jay |date=July 17, 2016 |website=Comicbook.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161024044505/http://comicbook.com/dc/2016/07/18/the-flash-season-2-soundtrack-details-announced |archive-date=October 24, 2016 |access-date=October 26, 2016}}</ref> The soundtrack for the second season was released digitally on July 22, 2016<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.watertower-music.com/releases/release.php?title=flash2 |title=The Flash: Original Television Soundtrack \u2013 Season 2 |website=WaterTower Music |publisher=WaterTower Music |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160819002607/http://www.watertower-music.com/releases/release.php?title=flash2 |archive-date=August 19, 2016 |access-date=August 3, 2016}}</ref> and in CD format on July 26, 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.lalalandrecords.com/Site/FlashS2.html |title=THE FLASH \u2013 SEASON 2 |website=La-La Land Records |publisher=La-La Land Records |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823013633/http://www.lalalandrecords.com/Site/FlashS2.html |archive-date=August 23, 2016 |access-date=August 3, 2016}}</ref> Neely also composed a theme when Gustin as Barry appeared on the eighteenth episode of ''Supergirl'', \"Worlds Finest\".<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=715087511005999104 |user=cowonthewall |title=Oh wow! Thank you for the love on #SupergirlXTheFlash! You're too kind. It was lots of fun. Expect some of it on the soundtrack this summer. |author=Blake Neely |date=March 30, 2016 |access-date=October 26, 2016}}</ref> The theme was titled \"World's Finest\" when it was released on the ''Supergirl: Season 1'' soundtrack.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2016/07/11/supergirl-season-1-soundtrack-details/ |title='Supergirl' Season 1 Soundtrack Details |date=July 11, 2016 |website=Film Music Reporter |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005182416/http://filmmusicreporter.com/2016/07/11/supergirl-season-1-soundtrack-details/ |archive-date=October 5, 2016 |access-date=October 26, 2016}}</ref>\n\nAll music composed by Blake Neely.<ref name=\"MusicS2\">{{Cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/flash-season-2-original-television/id1135604474 |title=The Flash: Season 2 (Original Television Soundtrack) |date=July 22, 2015 |website=[[iTunes]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170605153859/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/flash-season-2-original-television/id1135604474 |archive-date=June 5, 2017 |access-date=October 26, 2016}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| total_length    = 1:18:26\n| title1          = How It Ended / Reluctant Hero\n| length1         = 4:35\n| title2          = Harrison's Will / Henry Released\n| length2         = 2:54\n| title3          = Jay Garrick Warns of a Man Called Zoom\n| length3         = 2:20\n| title4          = Stein Explains a Multiverse\n| length4         = 2:00\n| title5          = Family of Rogues\n| length5         = 2:42\n| title6          = Joe Tells Iris the Truth About Her Mother\n| length6         = 2:51\n| title7          = The New Firestorm\n| length7         = 1:44\n| title8          = Staged Fight to Lure Zoom\n| length8         = 2:19\n| title9          = The Face of Your Hero\n| length9         = 2:59\n| title10         = Grodd into the Breach\n| length10        = 4:04\n| title11         = Vandal Savage Arrives\n| length11        = 1:50\n| title12         = Who Is Kendra? / Hawkman Cometh\n| length12        = 3:07\n| title13         = Savage Attack, a Legend Is Born\n| length13        = 3:05\n| title14         = You Have a Son, His Name Is Wally\n| length14        = 2:02\n| title15         = Let It Snow Villains\n| length15        = 3:04\n| title16         = Sending Reverse Flash Back / Wells Betrays\n| length16        = 4:56\n| title17         = Welcome to Earth-2\n| length17        = 2:42\n| title18         = Hello, Breachers\n| length18        = 2:06\n| title19         = Hunting and Electrifying King Shark\n| length19        = 2:21\n| title20         = The Right Decision\n| length20        = 3:47\n| title21         = Who Is Hunter Zolomon?\n| length21        = 2:36\n| title22         = Ready to Save the World\n| length22        = 4:07\n| title23         = Stuck in the Speed Force\n| length23        = 3:54\n| title24         = Black Siren in Central City\n| length24        = 2:28\n| title25         = The Race of His Life\n| length25        = 3:59\n| title26         = I Will Wait for You\n| length26        = 3:54\n}}\n\n=== Arrowverse tie-ins ===\nIn October 2015, ''Arrow'' showrunner [[Wendy Mericle]] revealed that the producers of the [[Arrowverse]] had begun having someone track all the characters and plots used by each series, in order to make sure everything lines up,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/10/04/arrow-showrunner-on-season-4-introducing-damien-darhk-green-arrow-and-more-humor?page=2 |title=ARROW SHOWRUNNER ON SEASON 4 INTRODUCING DAMIEN DARHK, \"GREEN ARROW\" AND MORE HUMOR |last=Goldman |first=Eric |date=October 4, 2015 |website=IGN |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151008000544/http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/10/04/arrow-showrunner-on-season-4-introducing-damien-darhk-green-arrow-and-more-humor?page=2 |archive-date=October 8, 2015 |access-date=October 4, 2015}}</ref> though Aaron Helbing noted in April 2016 that \"sometimes the schedules don't line up exactly...and that stuff is out of our control\", such as when Barry is shown using his abilities on ''Arrow'' that month, while not having them the same week on ''The Flash''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2016/04/26/castle-season-9-spoilers-rick-los-angeles-move/ |title=Matt's Inside Line: Scoop on Castle, Grey's, Once, Grimm, The Flash, Bones, Reign, P.D., Secrets and Lies and More |last=Mitovich |first=Matt Webb |date=April 26, 2012 |website=[[TVLine]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427110031/http://tvline.com/2016/04/26/castle-season-9-spoilers-rick-los-angeles-move/ |archive-date=April 27, 2016 |access-date=April 28, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe second season of ''The Flash'' began to explore the concept of the multiverse, by introducing Earth-2, which features [[doppelg\u00e4nger]]s of the inhabitants in the Arrowverse (or Earth-1).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cinemablend.com/television/Flash-Feature-Earth-2-Earlier-Than-Expected-77097.html |title=The Flash Will Feature Earth 2 Earlier Than Expected |last=Holmes |first=Adam |date=August 7, 2015 |website=Cinema Blend |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160216060518/http://www.cinemablend.com/television/Flash-Feature-Earth-2-Earlier-Than-Expected-77097.html |archive-date=February 16, 2016 |access-date=February 10, 2016}}</ref> In \"Welcome to Earth-2\" of ''The Flash'', glimpses of the multiverse are seen, including an image of ''Supergirl'' star [[Melissa Benoist]] as [[Kara Zor-El (Arrowverse)|Supergirl]] and an image of [[John Wesley Shipp]] as the Flash from the [[The Flash (1990 TV series)|1990 television series]], implying that those two television series exist on alternate Earths to the Arrowverse.<ref name=\"MultiverseSupergirl\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/surprising-dc-superhero-makes-cameo-flash |title=Surprising DC Superhero Makes Cameo On \"The Flash\" |last=Couto |first=Anthony |date=February 9, 2016 |website=[[Comic Book Resources]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160212195031/http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/surprising-dc-superhero-makes-cameo-flash |archive-date=February 12, 2016 |access-date=February 9, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/flash-teases-dc-tv-future-retro-continuity-with-multiple-surprise-cameos |title=\"Flash\" Teases DC TV Future, Retro Continuity With Multiple Surprise Cameos |last=Couto |first=Anthony |date=February 9, 2016 |website=[[Comic Book Resources]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160211090040/http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/flash-teases-dc-tv-future-retro-continuity-with-multiple-surprise-cameos |archive-date=February 11, 2016 |access-date=February 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe second annual two-way crossover with ''Arrow'' aired on December 1 and 2, 2015, where the Flash and the Green Arrow team up to take on Vandal Savage, who is looking for Kendra Saunders and Carter Hall, the reincarnations of Hawkgirl and Hawkman.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/sdcc-interview-cast-crew-divulge-secrets-of-the-flash-season-2 |title=SDCC INTERVIEW: CAST, CREW DIVULGE SECRETS OF \"THE FLASH\" SEASON 2 |last=Amaya |first=Erik |date=July 16, 2015 |website=Comic Book Resources |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150717143038/http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/sdcc-interview-cast-crew-divulge-secrets-of-the-flash-season-2 |archive-date=July 17, 2015 |access-date=July 16, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"eonlineCrossover2\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/678116/spoiler-chat-scoop-on-american-horror-story-pretty-little-liars-arrow-the-mindy-project-and-more |title=Spoiler Chat: Scoop on American Horror Story, Pretty Little Liars, Arrow, The Mindy Project and More! |date=July 21, 2015 |website=E! Online |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150723073754/http://www.eonline.com/news/678116/spoiler-chat-scoop-on-american-horror-story-pretty-little-liars-arrow-the-mindy-project-and-more |archive-date=July 23, 2015 |access-date=July 22, 2015}}</ref> Though ''[[Legends of Tomorrow]]'' did not have an episode as part of the 2015\u201316 crossover, the ''Arrow'' and ''The Flash'' episodes from this event did set up a number of characters who star and recur in that series.<ref name=\"Aug2015CB\">{{Cite web |url=http://comicbook.com/2015/08/04/casper-crump-to-play-vandal-savage-on-legends-of-tomorrow-arrow-/ |title=Casper Crump to Play Vandal Savage on Legends of Tomorrow, Arrow and The Flash |last=Burlingame |first=Russ |date=August 4, 2015 |website=Comicbook.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150806155703/http://comicbook.com/2015/08/04/casper-crump-to-play-vandal-savage-on-legends-of-tomorrow-arrow- |archive-date=August 6, 2015 |access-date=August 5, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"HawkmanRegular\">{{Cite web |url=http://comicbook.com/2015/08/23/hawkman-confirmed-as-regular-part-of-legends-of-tomorrow/ |title=Hawkman Confirmed As Regular Part of Legends of Tomorrow |last=Burlingame |first=Russ |date=August 23, 2015 |website=Comicbook.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150824133003/http://comicbook.com/2015/08/23/hawkman-confirmed-as-regular-part-of-legends-of-tomorrow/ |archive-date=August 24, 2015 |access-date=December 2, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"eonlineCrossover2\" /> [[Casper Crump]], [[Falk Hentschel]] and [[Peter Francis James]] debut in the crossover, as [[Vandal Savage (Arrowverse)|Vandal Savage]], [[Carter Hall (Arrowverse)|Carter Hall / Hawkman]], and Dr. [[Aldus Boardman]], respectively.<ref name=\"Crump\" /><ref name=\"Hentschel\" /><ref name=\"James1\">{{Cite web |url=http://comicbook.com/2015/09/24/exclusive-legends-of-tomorrow-casts-peter-francis-james-as-key-p/ |title=EXCLUSIVE: Legends of Tomorrow Casts Peter Francis James As Key Part of Hawkman/Hawkgirl Story |last=Burlingame |first=Russ |date=September 24, 2015 |website=Comicbook.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161205032204/http://comicbook.com/2015/09/24/exclusive-legends-of-tomorrow-casts-peter-francis-james-as-key-p/ |archive-date=December 5, 2016 |access-date=September 24, 2015}}</ref> ScreenRant's Alice Walker discussed how the annual ''Arrow/The Flash'' crossover suffered from also trying to set up Legends, which was \"too much to ask from the already crowded storylines and ended up feeling like an exercise in synchronicity, with producers planting more seeds than they could reap. The crossover event was no longer a fun way to contrast the two shows; it now had to serve the much larger purpose of setting up an entirely new world.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://screenrant.com/legends-tomorrow-arrow-flash-plots/ |title=How Legends of Tomorrow Has Hurt Arrow & The Flash |last=Walker |first=Alice |date=January 20, 2016 |website=[[Screen Rant]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170408004114/http://screenrant.com/legends-tomorrow-arrow-flash-plots/ |archive-date=April 8, 2017 |access-date=January 23, 2016}}</ref>\n<!-- * http://comicbook.com/2015/07/12/flash-season-two-ep-andrew-kriesberg-confirms-new-rogues-grodds-/\n* http://www.spoilertv.com/2015/11/the-flash-arrow-crossover-interview.html\n* http://comicbook.com/2016/01/06/exclusive-arrows-diggle-to-help-the-flash-take-on-king-shark/\n* http://ca.ign.com/articles/2016/01/28/arrow-david-ramsey-on-argus-diggles-new-helmet-and-the-flash-crossover\n* http://www.cinemablend.com/television/Why-Flash-Was-Able-Run-Funeral-Arrow-133877.html\n** http://tvline.com/2016/04/26/castle-season-9-spoilers-rick-los-angeles-move/\n* http://collider.com/the-flash-arrow-crossover-greg-berlanti-andrew-kreisberg-interview/\n* http://collider.com/arrow-the-flash-crossover-legends-of-tomorrow-cast/ -->\n\n==== Crossover with ''Supergirl'' ====\nIn February 2016, it was announced that Gustin would appear on the eighteenth episode of ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]'', with Berlanti and Kreisberg, also ''Supergirl'' executive producers, thanking \"the fans and journalists who have kept asking for this to happen. It is our pleasure and hope to create an episode worthy of everyone's enthusiasm and support.\"<ref name=\"GustinSupergirl\">{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/flash-supergirl-crossover-cbs-grant-gustin-melissa-benoist-1201695949/ |title='The Flash' and 'Supergirl' to Unite for Crossover Episode on CBS |last=Prudom |first=Laura |website=Variety |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160204091618/https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/flash-supergirl-crossover-cbs-grant-gustin-melissa-benoist-1201695949/ |archive-date=February 4, 2016 |access-date=February 3, 2016}}</ref> While no plot details on the episodes were released at the time, Ross A. Lincoln of ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' noted that \"the in-universe reason\" for the crossover was due to Barry's ability to travel to various dimensions, thus implying that ''Supergirl'' exists on an alternate Earth to the Arrowverse in a multiverse.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/02/supergirl-the-flash-crossover-official-in-march-1201695796/ |title=Crossover Confirmed: 'The Flash' To Meet 'Supergirl' In March Episode |last=Lincoln |first=Ross A. |date=February 3, 2016 |website=Deadline Hollywood |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160204034257/http://deadline.com/2016/02/supergirl-the-flash-crossover-official-in-march-1201695796/ |archive-date=February 4, 2016 |access-date=February 3, 2016}}</ref> \"Welcome to Earth-2\" confirmed this, showing an image of Benoist as Supergirl during a sequence where characters travel through that multiverse.<ref name=\"MultiverseSupergirl\" /> The Earth that the series inhabits has been informally referred to as \"Earth-CBS\" by [[Marc Guggenheim]], one of the creators of ''Arrow''.<ref name=\"GuggenheimOct2016\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/10/18/arrow-crossover-100-episode-spoilers |title=Arrow boss teases 100th episode, crossover catalyst |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=October 18, 2016 |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021095428/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/10/18/arrow-crossover-100-episode-spoilers |archive-date=October 21, 2016 |access-date=October 18, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn \"[[Worlds Finest]]\", which aired on CBS on March 28, 2016, ''Supergirl'' is established as being in an alternate universe where the Flash helps Kara fight the Silver Banshee and Livewire in exchange for her help in returning home.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/03/09/the-flash-and-supergirl-crossover-poster-and-plot-description-revealed |title=THE FLASH AND SUPERGIRL CROSSOVER POSTER AND PLOT DESCRIPTION REVEALED |last=Goldman |first=Eric |date=March 9, 2016 |website=[[IGN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160309193127/http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/03/09/the-flash-and-supergirl-crossover-poster-and-plot-description-revealed |archive-date=March 9, 2016 |access-date=March 9, 2016}}</ref> The episode title was inspired by the ''[[World's Finest Comics]]'' series, in which [[Superman]] would team up with various other DC superheroes, including the Flash. The events of this episode take place between two moments in the eighteenth episode of ''The Flash'' season two, \"[[Versus Zoom]]\", which aired on April 19, 2016, in which Barry enters and exits a breach while wearing the tachyon device seen in this episode.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/03/18/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers |title=Supergirl-Flash crossover: Everything you need to know, straight from set |date=March 18, 2016 |website=Entertainment Weekly |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320153150/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/03/18/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers |archive-date=March 20, 2016 |access-date=December 3, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/03/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers-melissa-benoist-grant-gustin-andrew-kreisberg-cw-cbs-1201727447/ |title='Supergirl'-'Flash' Crossover: EP Andrew Kreisberg On How It Came Together |last=Dominic Patten |website=Deadline Hollywood |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520031339/http://deadline.com/2016/03/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers-melissa-benoist-grant-gustin-andrew-kreisberg-cw-cbs-1201727447/ |archive-date=May 20, 2016 |access-date=December 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cinemablend.com/television/Why-Didn-t-Flash-Talk-About-Supergirl-Crossover-All-132957.html |title=Why Didn't The Flash Talk About The Supergirl Crossover at All? |last=Holmes |first=Adam |date=April 22, 2016 |website=Cinema Blend |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160425045644/http://www.cinemablend.com/television/Why-Didn-t-Flash-Talk-About-Supergirl-Crossover-All-132957.html |archive-date=April 25, 2016 |access-date=April 25, 2016}}</ref> The crossover required \"a lot more logistical trickery\" than the usual Arrowverse crossovers due to Gustin filming ''The Flash'' in [[Vancouver]] alongside ''Arrow'' and ''Legends of Tomorrow'', while ''Supergirl'' is produced in [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tvinsider.com/article/70539/the-flash-grant-gustin-to-guest-star-on-supergirl/ |title=''The Flash'' Heads to ''Supergirl'' |last=Holbrook |first=Damian |date=February 3, 2016 |website=TV Insider |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160205230502/http://www.tvinsider.com/article/70539/the-flash-grant-gustin-to-guest-star-on-supergirl/ |archive-date=February 5, 2016 |access-date=February 4, 2016}}</ref> The producers chose to use the Flash as the character to crossover, due to his ability to travel between various Earths, and because it was \"a little more fun at first to bring the veteran from that show to the chemistry of a new show.\" Berlanti stated that \"in a perfect world\", the crossover would have featured both Gustin and Amell's Green Arrow, \"but logistically that would have been a nightmare to try and do both shows. We had to facilitate one.\"<ref name=\"THRSupergirlCrossover\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers-878275 |title=7 Things to Know About 'Supergirl's' Crossover With 'The Flash' |last=Bucksbaum |first=Sydney |date=March 25, 2016 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328183927/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers-878275 |archive-date=March 28, 2016 |access-date=March 29, 2016}}</ref> Gustin was optimistic that the crossover in 2016 would allow another crossover the following year with the rest of the Arrowverse shows.<ref name=\"EWSupergirlCrossover\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/03/18/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers |title=On the set: Everything you need to know about the Flash-Supergirl crossover |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=March 18, 2016 |website=Entertainment Weekly |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320153150/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/03/18/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers |archive-date=March 20, 2016 |access-date=March 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe crossover episode received excellent reviews. Cliff Wheatley of IGN gave the episode an 8.6/10, stating \"After the grim 'n' gritty ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice|Batman v Superman]]'', ''Supergirl''{{'s}} \"Worlds Finest\" offered a fun, upbeat palette cleanser and one of the series' strongest episodes to date. Instead of the usual \"beatdown\" introduction, Supergirl and the Flash went straight to being superfriends, which was refreshing. Not only did Barry Allen fit perfectly in Kara's world, but actors Grant Gustin and Melissa Benoist had fantastic chemistry together onscreen. While the city's turnaround on Supergirl's Red K incident was a little sudden, overall, \"Worlds Finest\" was delightful.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/03/29/supergirl-worlds-finest-review |title=\"SUPERGIRL: \"Worlds Finest\" REVIEW\" |date=March 29, 2016 |website=[[IGN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160330072727/http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/03/29/supergirl-worlds-finest-review |archive-date=March 30, 2016 |access-date=March 29, 2016}}</ref> Stacy Glanzman of TV Fanatic gave the episode a 5.0 out of 5 stars.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tvfanatic.com/2016/03/supergirl-season-1-episode-18-review-worlds-finest/ |title=Supergirl Season 1 Episode 18 Review: Worlds Finest |date=March 28, 2016 |website=TV Fanatic |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160401232004/http://www.tvfanatic.com/2016/03/supergirl-season-1-episode-18-review-worlds-finest/ |archive-date=April 1, 2016 |access-date=March 28, 2016}}</ref>\n<!-- https://tvline.com/2016/03/25/supergirl-flash-crossover-spoilers-kara-on-earth-1/ -->\n\n== Marketing ==\n''The Flash'' surged 1,378% in buzz (highest year over year growth in conversation) from last year for its second season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.adweek.com/tv-video/these-new-and-returning-fall-tv-shows-are-getting-most-buzz-twitter-166970/ |title=These New and Returning Fall TV Shows Are Getting the Most Buzz on Twitter |last=Baysinger |first=Tim |date=September 17, 2015 |website=[[Adweek]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181203211346/https://www.adweek.com/tv-video/these-new-and-returning-fall-tv-shows-are-getting-most-buzz-twitter-166970/ |archive-date=December 3, 2018 |access-date=December 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n\n=== Broadcast ===\nThe season premiered on [[The CW]] on October 6, 2015,<ref name=\"2.01\" /> and ran until May 24, 2016.<ref name=\"2.23\" />\n\n=== Home media ===\nThe season began streaming on [[Netflix]] on October 4, 2016,<ref name=\"S2Netflix\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.tvguide.com/news/netflix-october-2016-leaving-new-arrivals/ |title=Netflix October: What's Coming and Leaving |last=Mathews |first=Liam |date=September 22, 2016 |website=[[TV Guide]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027123219/http://www.tvguide.com/news/netflix-october-2016-leaving-new-arrivals/ |archive-date=October 27, 2016 |access-date=October 27, 2016}}</ref> and was released on [[Blu-ray]] and [[DVD]] in [[DVD region code#Region codes and countries|Region 1]] on September 6, 2016.<ref name=\"s2R1_A\" />\n{{Television home release\n| color = 1D2229\n| title = The Flash: The Complete Second Season\n| set_details = \n* 23 episodes and includes the ''Arrow'' crossover episode \"Legends of Yesterday\"\n* 6-disc DVD set/4-disc Blu-ray set\n* English (Dolby Digital 5.1 Surround)\n* English [[Dubtitle|SDH]], Spanish and French subtitles\n* Subtitles: English\n| special_features = \n* 2015 Comic-Con Panel\n* 2015 PaleyFest\n* Deleted Scenes\n* Gag Reel\n* Behind-the-scenes visual effects featurettes for almost every episode\n* Featurettes\n** Star Crossed Hawks\n** Star Crossed Hawks: The Hunt for Vandal Savage\n** The Many Faces of Zoom\n** Chasing Flash \u2013 The Journey of Kevin Smith\n| region1 = September 6, 2016<ref name=\"s2R1_A\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Flash-Season-2-Press-Release/22316 |title=The Flash on DVD |last=Lambert |first=David |date=May 31, 2016 |website=TVShowsOnDVD.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170208114927/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Flash-Season-2-Press-Release/22316 |archive-date=February 8, 2017 |access-date=December 3, 2018}}</ref>\n| region2 = September 12, 2016<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/product/B018I8RFLM/ref=pd_bxgy_74_img_2?ie=UTF8&psc=1&refRID=X0X8RSVN38TWF4H2H2N5 |title=The Flash \u2013 Season 2 [DVD] [2016] |website=Amazon.co.uk |access-date=December 3, 2018}}</ref>\n| region4 = September 7, 2016<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ezydvd.com.au/DVD/flash-the-season-2/dp/6175762 |title=The Flash \u2013 Season 2 [DVD] |website=EzyDVD |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220043102/http://www.ezydvd.com.au/DVD/flash-the-season-2/dp/6175762 |archive-date=December 20, 2016 |access-date=December 3, 2018}}</ref>\n| regionA = September 6, 2016<ref name=\"s2R1_A\" />\n| regionB = September 12, 2016<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/product/B018I8RG84/ref=pd_cp_74_3?ie=UTF8&psc=1&refRID=0RMF152YCW02Z2HYX0J7 |title=The Flash \u2013 Season 2 [Blu-ray] [2016] |website=Amazon.co.uk |access-date=December 3, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n=== Copyright infringement ===\nThe second season of ''The Flash'' was the fourth most-[[Torrent file|torrented]] television show of 2016.<ref name=\"thirdfreak\">{{Cite web |url=https://torrentfreak.com/game-of-thrones-most-torrented-tv-show-of-2016-161226/ |title='Game of Thrones' Most Torrented TV-Show of 2016 |last=Van der Sar |first=Ernesto |date=December 26, 2016 |website=[[TorrentFreak]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161226175113/https://torrentfreak.com/game-of-thrones-most-torrented-tv-show-of-2016-161226/ |archive-date=December 26, 2016 |access-date=December 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Ratings ===\nThe second season finished as the 112th ranked show, with an average viewership of 4.25&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/05/tv-season-2015-2016-series-rankings-shows-full-list-1201763189/ |title=Full 2015\u201316 TV Season Series Rankings: 'Blindspot', 'Life In Pieces' & 'Quantico' Lead Newcomers |last=de Moraes |first=Lisa |date=May 26, 2016 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6ho7kEKye?url=http://deadline.com/2016/05/tv-season-2015-2016-series-rankings-shows-full-list-1201763189/ |archive-date=May 27, 2016 |access-date=May 27, 2016}}</ref>\n{{Television episode ratings\n| width    = 99\n| title1   = [[#ep24|The Man Who Saved Central City]]\n| date1    = October 6, 2015\n| rs1      = 1.4/5\n| viewers1 = 3.58<ref name=\"2.01\" />\n| dvr1     = 1.0\n| dvrv1    = 2.35\n| total1   = 2.4\n| totalv1  = 5.93<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/31/broadcast-live-7-ratings-week-3-quantico-more-than-doubles-empire-and-blindspot-score-biggest-gains/ |title=Broadcast Live +7 ratings, week 3: 'Quantico' more than doubles, 'Empire' and 'Blindspot' score biggest gains |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=October 31, 2015 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6cZoSk5KN?url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/10/26/broadcast-live-7-ratings-week-3-2015-16/480276/ |archive-date=October 26, 2015 |access-date=October 31, 2015}}</ref>\n\n| title2   = [[#ep25|Flash of Two Worlds]]\n| date2    = October 13, 2015\n| rs2      = 1.4/4\n| viewers2 = 3.49<ref name=\"2.02\" />\n| dvr2     = 0.8\n| dvrv2    = 2.06\n| total2   = 2.2\n| totalv2  = 5.52<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/11/04/broadcast-live-7-ratings-week-4-jane-the-virgin-premiere-doubles-empire-and-blindspot-top-charts-for-oct-12-18/ |title=Broadcast Live +7 ratings, week 4: 'Jane the Virgin' premiere doubles, 'Empire' and 'Blindspot' top charts for Oct. 12\u201318 |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=November 4, 2015 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.