RbwTy?url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/05/09/broadcast-live-7-ratings-april-18-24-2016/ |archive-date=May 10, 2016 |access-date=May 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\n| title19   = [[#ep42|Back to Normal]]\n| date19    = April 26, 2016\n| rs19      = 1.3/5\n| viewers19 = 3.39<ref name=\"2.19\" />\n| dvr19     = 0.8\n| dvrv19    = 1.86\n| total19   = 2.1\n| totalv19  = 5.26<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/05/17/broadcast-live-7-ratings-april-25-may-1-2016/ |title=Broadcast Live +7 ratings: 'Big Bang Theory,' 'Empire' and 'Blacklist' lead for April 25-May 1 |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=May 17, 2016 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6ha5IGARo?url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/05/17/broadcast-live-7-ratings-april-25-may-1-2016/ |archive-date=May 17, 2016 |access-date=May 23, 2016}}</ref>\n\n| title20   = [[#ep43|Rupture]]\n| date20    = May 3, 2016\n| rs20      = 1.3/5\n| viewers20 = 3.34<ref name=\"2.20\" />\n| dvr20     = 0.8\n| dvrv20    = 1.92\n| total20   = 2.1\n| totalv20  = 5.25<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/05/23/broadcast-live-7-ratings-may-2-8-2016/ |title=Broadcast Live +7 ratings: 'Big Bang Theory' tops total gains, 'Vampire Diaries' and 9 others double in 18-49 |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=May 23, 2016 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6hjDQbKcQ?url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/05/23/broadcast-live-7-ratings-may-2-8-2016/ |archive-date=May 23, 2016 |access-date=May 23, 2016}}</ref>\n\n| title21   = [[#ep44|The Runaway Dinosaur]]\n| date21    = May 10, 2016\n| rs21      = 1.3/5\n| viewers21 = 3.52<ref name=\"2.21\" />\n| dvr21     = 0.8\n| dvrv21    = 1.82\n| total21   = 2.1\n| totalv21  = 5.34<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/05/31/broadcast-live-7-ratings-may-9-15-2016/ |title=Broadcast Live +7 ratings: 'Big Bang Theory' finale and 'Empire' share lead for May 9\u201315 |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=May 31, 2016 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160601134556/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/05/31/broadcast-live-7-ratings-may-9-15-2016/ |archive-date=June 1, 2016 |access-date=May 31, 2016}}</ref>\n\n| title22   = [[#ep45|Invincible]]\n| date22    = May 17, 2016\n| rs22      = 1.3/5\n| viewers22 = 3.37<ref name=\"2.22\" />\n| dvr22     = 0.9\n| dvrv22    = 2.08\n| total22   = 2.2\n| totalv22  = 5.45<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/06/06/broadcast-live-7-ratings-may-16-22-2016/ |title=Broadcast Live +7 ratings: 'Empire' and 'Blacklist' finales lead the week May 16\u201322 |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=June 6, 2016 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6iCCfLuUv?url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/06/06/broadcast-live-7-ratings-may-16-22-2016/ |archive-date=June 11, 2016 |access-date=May 31, 2016}}</ref>\n\n| title23   = [[#ep46|The Race of His Life]]\n| date23    = May 24, 2016\n| rs23      = 1.3/5\n| viewers23 = 3.35<ref name=\"2.23\" />\n| dvr23     = 0.6\n| dvrv23    = 1.49\n| total23   = 1.9\n| totalv23  = 4.85<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/06/13/broadcast-live-7-ratings-may-23-29-2016/ |title=Broadcast Live +7 ratings: 'Blindspot' leads for May 23\u201329 as summer slowdown begins |last=Porter |first=Rick |date=June 13, 2016 |website=TV by the Numbers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614122227/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/06/13/broadcast-live-7-ratings-may-23-29-2016/ |archive-date=June 14, 2016 |access-date=June 13, 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n\n=== Critical response ===\nThe [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reported a 94% approval rating for the second season with an average rating of 7.84/10, based on 24 reviews. The website's consensus reads, \"With distinctive visuals and a terrific cast, ''The Flash'' remains one of the strongest comic book shows on television.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/flash/s02/ |title=The Flash: Season 2 |date=December 9, 2019 |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215090357/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/flash/s02/ |archive-date=December 15, 2018 |access-date=December 15, 2018}}</ref> [[Metacritic]], which uses a weighted average, assigned the season a score of 81 out of 100, based on 4 reviews, indicating \"universal acclaim\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/the-flash-2014/season-2 |title=The Flash (2014) : Season 2 |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151004133606/http://www.metacritic.com/tv/the-flash-2014/season-2 |archive-date=October 4, 2015 |access-date=October 5, 2015}}</ref>\n\nReviewing for [[Collider (website)|Collider]], Dave Trumbore gave the season premiere a rating of 4 stars out of 5, saying, \"All in all, a very good way to start season two after the strong run of season one.\"<ref name=\"collider S02E1 review\" /> Mike Cecchini of ''[[Den of Geek!]]'' meanwhile rated the episode 3.5 stars out of 5, criticizing the episode's \"unsettled\" and \"rushed\" nature. He felt that the episode \"seems so focused on getting this season off to a running start that it [...] doesn't give events time to breathe.\"<ref name=\"201Cecchini\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.denofgeek.com/us/tv/the-flash/249580/the-flash-season-2-premiere-review-the-man-who-saved-central-city |title=The Flash Season 2 Premiere Review: The Man Who Saved Central City |last=Cecchini |first=Mike |date=October 6, 2015 |website=[[Den of Geek!]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181218054522/https://www.denofgeek.com/us/tv/the-flash/249580/the-flash-season-2-premiere-review-the-man-who-saved-central-city |archive-date=December 18, 2018 |access-date=December 17, 2018}}</ref> Erik Kain of ''[[Forbes]]'' noted a \"very big piece\" missing in the absence of Harrison Wells, but felt that the episode was \"an excellent start to the sophomore season of the CW\u2019s best super hero show.\"<ref name=\"201Kain\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2015/10/06/the-flash-season-2-premiere-review-the-man-who-saved-central-city/#36e99069395c |title='The Flash' Season 2 Premiere Review: 'The Man Who Saved Central City' |last=Kain |first=Erik |date=October 6, 2015 |website=[[Forbes]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181218054547/https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2015/10/06/the-flash-season-2-premiere-review-the-man-who-saved-central-city/#36e99069395c |archive-date=December 18, 2018 |access-date=December 17, 2018}}</ref> Although Henry Allen's abrupt exit was a common point of criticism amongst reviewers, Trumbore nevertheless felt that it was \"a small price to pay for an otherwise cohesive, entertaining, and emotionally satisfying episode.\"<ref name=\"collider S02E1 review\" /><ref name=\"201Kain\" /><ref name=\"201Cecchini\" />\n\nThe episode \"Welcome to Earth-2\" received a number of positive reviews. Erik Kain said that it was \"''The Flash'' at its best. An engaging, funny, scary episode that hits all the right notes from start to finish.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2016/02/10/the-flash-season-2-episode-13-review-earth-two-where-all-of-barrys-fantasies-come-true/#32ed152457a9 |title='The Flash' Season 2, Episode 13 Review: Earth Two, Where All Of Barry's Dreams Come True |last=Kain |first=Erik |date=February 10, 2016 |website=[[Forbes]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160714123334/http://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2016/02/10/the-flash-season-2-episode-13-review-earth-two-where-all-of-barrys-fantasies-come-true/#32ed152457a9 |archive-date=July 14, 2016 |access-date=December 16, 2018}}</ref> [[IGN]]'s Jesse Schedeen rated it 9.7 out of 10, praising the concept of Earth-2, Barry's dramatic moments, the depiction of Deathstorm, Killer Frost, and Reverb, but criticized the need to kill off Reverb so soon. He concluded, \"''The Flash'' delivered one of its best episodes yet as Barry and friends took a hilarious but emotional trip to Earth-2.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2016/02/10/the-flash-welcome-to-earth-2-review |title=The Flash: \"Welcome to Earth-2\" Review |last=Schedeen |first=Jesse |date=February 9, 2016 |website=[[IGN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180310084000/http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/02/10/the-flash-welcome-to-earth-2-review |archive-date=March 10, 2018 |access-date=December 16, 2018}}</ref> Angelica Jade Basti\u00e9n of ''[[Vulture.com|Vulture]]'' said the episode \"marries incredible action sequences, amazing direction by Millicent Shelton, some of the cast's best acting (particularly from Candice Patton and Grant Gustin), lots of heart, and just the right number of nods to the comics. It is undoubtedly the best episode of the season, and just may be the best episode of ''The Flash'' yet.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2016/02/flash-recap-season-2-episode-13.html |title=The Flash Recap: Through the Looking Glass |last=Basti\u00e9n |first=Angelica Jade |date=February 10, 2016 |website=[[Vulture.com|Vulture]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170204094617/http://www.vulture.com/2016/02/flash-recap-season-2-episode-13.html |archive-date=February 4, 2017 |access-date=December 16, 2018}}</ref> Dave Trumbore rated the episode 4 stars out of 5, saying, \"This was an absolutely insane episode of ''The Flash'', and that's saying something since this show is normally fast-paced and full of Easter eggs even on a relatively slow week.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://collider.com/the-flash-recap-welcome-to-earth-2/ |title='The Flash' Recap: \"Welcome to Earth-2'' - It's Zoom's World and We're Just Living In It |last=Trumbore |first=Dave |date=February 9, 2016 |website=Collider |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615214450/http://collider.com/the-flash-recap-welcome-to-earth-2/ |archive-date=June 15, 2018 |access-date=December 17, 2018}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''{{'}}s Jonathon Dornbush praised the scene where Barry talks to his Earth-2 doppelg\u00e4nger's mother over phone, saying Gustin \"has proved mightily adept at tackling Barry's grief, hope, and the many other emotions swirling around in regard to his mother and her death.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ew.com/recap/the-flash-season-2-episode-13/ |title='The Flash' recap: Doppelgangers, death, and more drama await on Earth-2 |last=Dornbush |first=Jonathon |date=February 10, 2016 |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180403114649/http://ew.com/recap/the-flash-season-2-episode-13/ |archive-date=April 3, 2018 |access-date=December 17, 2018}}</ref> Scott Von Doviak of ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' said, \"Since its return from hiatus, ''The Flash'' has been sluggish and morose, and the Zoom arc has fizzled. 'Welcome to Earth-2' jump-starts both the storyline and the season as a whole [...and] is just about as good as ''The Flash'' gets.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://tv.avclub.com/the-flash-visits-earth-2-in-a-whirlwind-episode-that-jo-1798186588 |title=The Flash visits Earth-2 in a whirlwind episode that jolts the season back to life |last=Doviak |first=Scott Von |date=February 9, 2016 |website=[[The A.V. Club]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181218143615/https://tv.avclub.com/the-flash-visits-earth-2-in-a-whirlwind-episode-that-jo-1798186588 |archive-date=December 18, 2018 |access-date=December 17, 2018}}</ref>\n\nReviewing the season finale, Allison Keene of Collider directed specific praise to Gustin's performance, saying \"Sometimes a great TV performer can come out of an already fantastic episode, but occasionally an actor can rise above the material, proving that even though the writers have let them down, the actor is going to make the most of what they\u2019ve been given. That\u2019s exactly where we find ourselves with ''The Flash''{{'}}s head-scratching finale, which capped off a largely enjoyable but ultimately uneven second season. What has never been in doubt, though, is star Grant Gustin\u2019s ability to convince viewers that this all makes sense in an emotional, earnest, and often light-hearted way.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://collider.com/tv-performer-of-the-week-grant-gustin-the-flash/ |title=TV Performer of the Week: Grant Gustin, 'The Flash' |last=Keene |first=Allison |date=May 27, 2016 |website=Collider |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181216104238/http://collider.com/tv-performer-of-the-week-grant-gustin-the-flash |archive-date=December 16, 2018 |access-date=December 16, 2018}}</ref> In his review for ''[[Nerdist]]'', Joseph McCabe concluded, \"For all this season's faults, most of which came from repeating the major villain arc of season one, [...] there were moments in the last handful of episodes where Barry demonstrated more independent thought than the show often allows him. Coming up with his own ideas, for example, to defeat the villain of the week rather than relying on his friends at STAR Labs. That's the Barry I want to see more of in season three.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nerdist.com/the-flash-season-finale-review-the-race-of-his-life/ |title=THE FLASH SEASON FINALE REVIEW: \"THE RACE OF HIS LIFE\" |last=McCabe |first=Joseph |date=May 25, 2016 |website=[[Nerdist]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181218054847/https://nerdist.com/the-flash-season-finale-review-the-race-of-his-life/ |archive-date=December 18, 2018 |access-date=December 17, 2018}}</ref>\n\nA number of critics felt that the season as a whole suffered from the standards set by its predecessor, calling it \"uneven\" and criticizing the handling of the season's main villain. Collider's Kayti Burt gave the season 3 stars out of 5, saying, \"''The Flash'' finished off an uneven season with an uneven finale that couldn\u2019t overcome the burden of an underdeveloped, illogical villain. With Zoom, ''The Flash'' fell victim to a common drama mistake of a contemporary TV era: it prioritized the plot twist over the well-developed character arc.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://collider.com/the-flash-season-2-finale-recap-the-race-of-his-life/ |title='The Flash' Season 2 Finale Recap: \"The Race of His Life\" |last=Burt |first=Kayti |date=May 24, 2016 |website=Collider |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180407033532/http://collider.com/the-flash-season-2-finale-recap-the-race-of-his-life |archive-date=April 7, 2018 |access-date=December 16, 2018}}</ref> Jeff Jensen of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' gave the season a \"B-\" grade, calling it \"certifiably slumptacular\" and said that the \"bold\" introduction of the multiverse did not meet his expectations. Jensen praised Barry's onscreen rapport with Joe but felt it was underutilized due to the introduction of Joe's biological son Wally, and criticized Barry's romantic fixation for Iris. He also criticized Zoom, saying, \"He began as an alluring mystery but lost zip over time\" and once his identity was revealed, \"became a weak embodiment of generic villainy\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://ew.com/article/2016/05/25/flash-season-2-review/ |title=The Flash season 2 review |last=Jensen |first=Jeff |date=March 28, 2017 |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |access-date=December 2, 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215090244/https://ew.com/article/2016/05/25/flash-season-2-review/ |archive-date=December 15, 2018}}</ref> Jesse Schedeen gave the entire season a rating of 8.6 out of 10, explaining, \"This season met and occasionally even exceeded the heights of its predecessor. But it was also a more uneven and ultimately more flawed experience in the end.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/06/01/the-flash-season-2-review |title=The Flash: Season 2 Review |last=Schedeen |first=Jesse |date=June 1, 2016 |website=[[IGN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026160323/http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/06/01/the-flash-season-2-review |archive-date=October 26, 2016 |access-date=December 15, 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Accolades ===\n''The Flash'' was included on multiple Best/Top TV Shows of 2015 lists, ranking on ''[[The Salt Lake Tribune]]''{{'}}s (4th), ''[[Omaha World-Herald]]''{{'}}s (7th), and ''[[IndieWire]]''{{'}}s (10th), as well as on un-ranked lists of ''[[Criticwire]]'' and ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/feature/critics-pick-the-top-10-best-tv-shows-of-2015 |title=Best of 2015: Television Critic Top Ten Lists |date=December 8, 2015 |website=Metacritic |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160706184930/http://www.metacritic.com/feature/critics-pick-the-top-10-best-tv-shows-of-2015 |archive-date=July 6, 2016}}</ref> In its second season, ''The Flash'' was nominated for 20 awards, winning five. The series was nominated for three [[Saturn Awards]], winning [[Saturn Award for Best Superhero Adaptation Television Series|Best Superhero Adaption Television Series]] for the second year in a row.<ref name=\"42nd Saturn Awards\" /> The show was also nominated for three [[Leo Awards]], winning again for Best Visual Effects in a Dramatic Series for the episode \"Gorilla Warfare\".<ref name=\"LeoAwards\" /> At the [[2016 Teen Choice Awards]], the show gained six nominations with Gustin winning for Choice TV Actor: Fantasy/Sci-Fi.<ref name=\"2016 Teen Choice Awards\" />\n<!-- * http://cwatlanta.cbslocal.com/2015/12/30/atlantas-cw-has-tvs-best-buzz/\n* http://collider.com/best-tv-2015-drama/#actor\n* http://collider.com/the-best-tv-episodes-of-2015/#the-flash-enter-zoom\n* http://collider.com/best-tv-2015-villains/\n* https://www.forbes.com/sites/insertcoin/2016/05/03/power-ranking-all-the-marvel-and-dc-superhero-shows-currently-on-television/#6b873bc4ae98 -->\n\n{{Awards table|5}}\n|-<section begin=Awards />\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"20\" | 2016\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[2016 Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Awards]]\n| [[Kids' Choice Award for Favorite TV Show|Favorite Family TV Show]]\n| ''The Flash''\n| {{Nom}}\n| <ref name=\"2016 Kids' Choice Awards\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6865874/taylor-swift-justin-bieber-receive-2016-nickelodeon-kids-choice-award |title=2016 Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Award Nominations: See List &#124; Billboard |last=Olson |first=Cathy |date=February 4, 2016 |work=Billboard |access-date=February 2, 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203113325/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6865874/taylor-swift-justin-bieber-receive-2016-nickelodeon-kids-choice-award |archive-date=February 3, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| Favorite Male TV Star \u2013 Family Show\n| [[Grant Gustin]]\n| {{Nom}}\n| <ref name=\"2016 Kids' Choice Awards\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Leo Awards]]\n| Best Direction in a Dramatic Series\n| J. J. Makaro (\"Enter Zoom\")\n| {{Nom}}\n| <ref name=\"2016 Leo Awards\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.leoawards.com/2016/nominees/by_program.php |title=Leo Awards, Nominees by Program 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160605064750/http://www.leoawards.com/2016/nominees/by_program.php |archive-date=June 5, 2016 |access-date=May 29, 2016}}</ref><br /><ref name=\"LeoAwards\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.leoawards.com/2016/winners/by_name_may_28.pdf |title=Winners by Evening May 28 |website=Leo Awards |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160615091643/http://www.leoawards.com/2016/winners/by_name_may_28.pdf |archive-date=June 15, 2016 |access-date=May 2